definitions.definition: The state or property of being synchronized .
examples: The generator went off line when it lost synchronization with the power line.

definitions.definition: The arrangement of military actions in time , space , and purpose to produce maximum relative combat power at a decisive place and time.

main_definition: The state or property of being synchronized .
secondary_definitions: ( military ) The arrangement of military actions in time , space , and purpose to produce maximum relative combat power at a decisive place and time.
